OL,3,CMan jailed after scamming fans with
OL,4,Cfake Champions League tickets
OL,6,FWaldron was jailed for 21 months at
OL,7,FLiverpool Crown Court after being
OL,8,Ffound guilty at trial for acquiring/
OL,9,Fusing/possessing criminal property.
OL,11,FHis associate, David Windsor, pleaded
OL,12,Fguilty to fraud offences in March 2024
OL,13,Fand was also jailed for 21 months.
OL,15,FDetective Chief Inspector Chris
OL,16,FMaddocks from the NWROCU's Economic
OL,17,FCrime Unit said: "The impact on the
OL,18,Fvictims in this case has been
OL,19,Fsignificant, and it highlights the
OL,20,Fimportance of purchasing tickets from
OL,21,Freputable sources.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/5
